    <h1>About Inventors' Workshops</h1>

    <p class="inner-container">
        With a team of engineers, scientists and educators, Inventors' Workshops provides curated information in different medias, 
        access to spaces, activities and passion-driven communities to learners and change-makers who want to efficiently learn 
        what they're passionate about and apply it to accomplish their dreams. Unlike just searching in Google for all resources 
        you need, we centralize them into one concise environment that reduces the search overhead and connects the passion-driven 
        community.
    </p>

    <h3>What is IW?</h3>

    <p>
        Inventors' Workshops is a transformative initiative to engage and train the STEAM (Science Technology Engineering Arts 
        and Math) leaders and enthusiasts of 2020 and 2100 today, through open-access to research, technology, opportunity, 
        and learning. Democratizing innovation calls for redesigning research and development processes to empower the 
        scientific and learning communities with tools and resources that invite them, as essential participants, to engage 
        in innovation practices.
    </p>

    <h3>Mission</h3>

    <p>
        ur mission is to help people of all ages and all learning levels by connecting them to the most relevant resources and 
        hands-on projects, to engage their interests, on a broad range of subjects so they have pathways to accelerate their 
        practical knowledge, experience, skills, expertise, and passion, today and throughout their lives.
    </p>

    <h3>Core Values</h3>

    <ul>
        <li>People of any age and knowledge level can drive their own education with discovery.</li>
        <li>Open access to expertise, resources, and activities.</li>
        <li>Transdisciplinarity creativity and innovation for life long and life wide learning, teaching, and discovery.</li>
    </ul>

